verses.text:
Enemies have ruined your country;
\q2 they have burned your towns, and there is no one left.
\q1 Foreigners plunder the crops in your fields while you watch;
\q2 they destroy everything that they see.
\q1

But the land is also full of idols;
\q2 the people worship things that they have made with their own hands.
\q1

Yahweh says, "I will appoint boys to be leaders;
\q2 young children will rule.
\q1

You people must tell the righteous people that good things will happen to them;
\q2 they will enjoy the blessings that they will receive for their good deeds.
\q1

Then Yahweh will send a cloud of smoke during the days and a flaming fire during the nights
to cover Jerusalem and all those who gather there;
it will be like a glorious canopy over the city.

Yahweh will humble everyone;
\q2 and he will humble everyone who is proud.
\q1

I and the children that Yahweh has given to me are like signs to warn the people of Israel;
\q2 we are warnings from Yahweh, commander of the angel armies,
\q2 the one who lives in his temple on Mount Zion in Jerusalem.

The Lord has warned the descendants of Jacob;
\q2 he has said that he will punish Israel.
\q1

Therefore, in one day Yahweh will get rid of those who are like Israel's head and those who are like its tail;
\q2 the ones who are like the top of the palm tree and the ones who are like the bottom.
\q1

The leaders of the people have misled them;
\q2 they have caused the people that they are ruling to be confused.
\q1

I am the Lord Yahweh, commander of the angel armies, who will send a plague among the best soldiers of Assyria;
\q2 it will be like a fire that will kill them and get rid of their glory.
\q1

There are glorious forests and fertile farmlands in Assyria, but Yahweh will completely destroy them;
\q2 they will be like a very sick person who shrivels up and then dies.
\q1

There will be very few trees left in those forests;
\q2 even a child will be able to count them."
\q1

One day in the future, Yahweh will cause the army of Assyria to stop oppressing you, his people;
\q2 he will end your suffering and your being slaves of the people of Assyria;
\q1 you will become too strong for them.
\q1

He will judge the cases of needy people fairly;
\q2 and he will act justly toward poor people.
\q1 He will punish evil people as a result of what he decides;
\q2 he will get rid of wicked people because of the evil things they have done.
\q1

He will always act righteously;
\q2 the good things he does will be like a belt around his waist.
\q1 He will always speak what is true;
\q2 the true words he speaks will be like a sash around his waist.
\b
\q1

When he becomes king, wolves and lambs will live together peacefully;
\q1 leopards, instead of killing baby goats,
\q2 will lie down with them.
\q1 Similarly, fat, healthy calves and lions will eat food together;
\q2 and a young child will take care of them.
\q1

Cows and bears will eat together;
\q2 bear cubs and calves will lie down together.
\q1 Lions will not eat other animals;
\q2 instead, they will eat hay like cows do.
\q1

No creatures will harm or kill other creatures on Mount Zion, my holy hill;
\q1 and the earth will be filled with people who know me,
\q2 as the seas are full of water.

Babylon has been a very beautiful city;
\q2 all the people of Babylonia have been very proud of Babylon, their capital city;
\q1 but God will destroy Babylon,
\q2 like he destroyed Sodom and Gomorrah.
\q1

You have disappeared from the earth like a star that fell from the sky;
\q1 you were very well known,
\q2 like the morning star is seen by everyone;
\q1 you destroyed many nations,
\q2 but now you have been destroyed.
\q1

The people of Dibon, the capital city, will go to their temple to mourn;
\q2 they will go to their high places set on the hilltops, and there they will weep.
\q1 They will wail because of what happened to Nebo and Medeba in the south;
\q2 they will all shave the hair of their heads, and the men will cut off their beards to show that they are grieving.
\q1

Throughout the country of Moab, people will be crying;
\q2 people as far away as Eglaim in the south and Beer Elim in the north will hear them wailing.
\q1

The women of Moab will be left alone at the fords of the Arnon River;
\q2 they will be like birds that have been pushed out of their nests.
\q1

We people of Judah have heard about the people of Moab;
\q2 we have heard that they are very proud and conceited;
\q1 they are insolent,
\q2 but what they say about themselves is not true.
\q1

People will no longer be glad at harvest time.
\q2 No one will sing in the vineyards;
\q1 no one will shout joyfully.
\q2 No one will tread on grapes to get grape juice for wine;
\q2 there will be nothing to shout about joyfully.
\q1

All the plants along the river and all the crops in the fields bordering the river will dry up;
\q2 then they will blow away and disappear.
\q1

Sail to Tarshish and tell them what happened;
\q2 weep, you people who live along the coast.
\q1

People from Tyre appointed kings over other places;
\q2 their traders were wealthy;
\q1 they were as powerful and wealthy as kings.
\q2 Who caused the people of Tyre to experience this disaster?
\q1

Everything on the earth will dry up and die;
\q2 its important people will become weak and unimportant.
\q1

The earth has become unacceptable to Yahweh because the people who live on it have disobeyed his laws;
\q2 they have rejected the covenant that he intends to last forever.
\q1

Towns and cities will be desolate;
\q2 every house will be locked to prevent thieves from entering, for no one will live in them.
\q1

Mobs will gather in the streets, wanting wine;
\q2 no one on the earth will be happy anymore.
\q1

Those in the west will sing with great happiness;
\q2 they will declare that Yahweh is very great.
\q1

Those in the east of Israel will also praise Yahweh;
\q2 those along the coastlines of the sea will praise Yahweh, the God the people Israel worship.
\q1

The earth will split apart and be shattered;
\q2 it will shake violently.
\q1

Yahweh, you are my God;
\q2 I will honor you and praise you.
\q1 You do wonderful things;
\q2 you said long ago that you would do those things,
\q2 and now you have done them as you said that you would.
\q1

Open the gates of the city for people who are righteous;
\q2 allow people who faithfully obey Yahweh to enter the city.
\q1

Yahweh, we desire that you will allow things to go well for us;
\q2 all that we have done is what you have enabled us to do.
\q1

Yahweh, when we were distressed, we asked you to help us;
\q2 when you disciplined us, we could barely speak out any prayer to you.
\q1

I am no longer angry with my people;
\q1 if any of your enemies try to injure you like briers and thorns injure people,
\q2 I will attack them in battle;
\q2 I will get rid of them completely,
\q1

There will be a time when the descendants of Jacob will prosper like a plant that has good roots;
\q2 they will be like trees that bud and blossom and bear a lot of fruit;
\q2 what they do will bless all the people in the world.
\b
\q1

The Israelite people are like dry branches on a tree;
\q2 women break them off and use them to make fires under their cooking pots.
\q1 Our Israelite people do not have any sense;
\q2 so Yahweh, who created them, will not act mercifully toward them
\q2 or be kind to them.

Terrible things will happen to the city of Samaria, the capital of Israel!
\q2 It is on a hill above a fertile valley;
\q1 the people who live there, who get drunk by drinking too much wine, are very proud;
\q2 it is a beautiful and glorious city,
\q2 but some day that beauty will disappear like a flower that wilts and dries up.
\q1

Listen to what I say;
\q2 pay attention carefully.
\q1

Also, farmers never thresh caraway with a heavy sledge;
\q2 instead, they beat it only with a stick.
\q1 Farmers never thresh cumin by driving a cart over it;
\q2 instead, they only hit it with a rod.
\q1

Terrible things will happen to those who try to conceal from me, Yahweh,
\q2 the evil things that they plan to do;
\q1 they do those deeds in the darkness
\q2 and they think, 'Yahweh certainly cannot see us;
\q2 he cannot know what we are doing!'
\q1

At that time, deaf people will be able to hear;
\q2 they will be able to hear when someone reads from a book;
\q1 and blind people will be able to see;
\q2 they will be able to see things when it is gloomy and even when it is dark.
\q1

But the result of your trusting in the king of Egypt is that you will be disappointed and disgraced;
\q2 because you trust in him, you will be humiliated.
\q1

but all those who trust in the king of Egypt will be humiliated,
\q2 because that nation will not be able to help you;
\q1 the treaty that you have made requesting help from them will be useless;
\q2 instead, the result will be that you will be humiliated and disgraced."

The promises made by the king of Egypt are worthless;
\q1 therefore I call Egypt 'Useless Rahab, the sea monster that does nothing.'
\q1

Therefore, the result of your sin of rejecting me will be that you will suddenly experience disasters;
\q2 what will happen to you will be like a cracked wall that suddenly collapses on you."
\q1

But Yahweh wants to act kindly toward you;
\q2 he is great because he desires to act mercifully.
\q1 Do not forget that Yahweh is a God who acts justly;
\q2 he is pleased with those who patiently trust in him.

It is as though we see Yahweh coming from far away;
\q2 he is extremely angry,
\q1 and there are thick clouds of smoke around him.
\q2 By what he says he shows that he is angry;
\q2 what he says is like a devastating fire.
\q1

The Valley of Topheth outside Jerusalem has been prepared for a long time;
\q2 it is ready for the king of Assyria;
\q1 the funeral pyre for burning his body is wide and high,
\q2 and it will be as though Yahweh will light the fire with his breath,
\q2 which will come out like a stream of burning sulfur.

Scoundrels do things that are evil and that deceive people;
\q2 they plan to do evil things;
\q1 by telling lies in court they cause poor people to have trouble,
\q2 even when what the poor people are requesting is fair.
\q1

When that happens, he will enable you to live securely;
\q2 he will fully protect your possessions,
\q2 he will enable you to be wise and to know all that you need to know;
\q1 and revering Yahweh will be like a valuable treasure that he will give to you.
\b
\q1

The sinners in Jerusalem will tremble because they are very afraid;
\q2 godless people will be terrified.
\q1 They say, "None of us can remain alive because this fire is burning everything;
\q2 it is like the fire on Yahweh's altar that will burn forever!"
\q1

Yahweh will be our mighty God;
\q1 he will be like a mighty river that will protect us
\q2 because our enemies will not be able to cross it;
\q2 no one will be able to row across it
\q2 and no warships will be able to sail across it.
\q1

There will be no more princes;
\q2 the people who have authority will have no kingdom to rule; the princes will disappear.
\q1

There will be a highway through that land;
\q2 it will be called 'the Holy Highway.'
\q1 People who are not acceptable to God will not walk on that road;
\q2 it will be only for those who conduct their lives as God wants them to,
\q2 and no wicked fools will walk on that road.
\q1

Those whom Yahweh has freed will return to Jerusalem;
\q1 they will sing as they enter the city,
\q2 and they will be extremely joyful forever.
\q1 No longer will they be sad or mourn;
\q2 they will be completely joyful and glad.

But I know everything about you;
\q2 I know when you are in your house and when you go outside;
\q2 I also know that you are raging against me.
\q1

But those who trust in Yahweh will become strong again;
\q2 it will be as though they will soar as eagles do.
\q1 They will run for a long time and not become weary;
\q2 they will walk long distances and not faint.

Who has urged this king to come from the east?
\q1 Who has commissioned this king to work for him? Whoever it is, he enabled his army to defeat many nations
\q2 and to trample their kings under his feet;
\q1 to cut their enemies into tiny pieces with their swords;
\q2 to make their enemies scatter with their bows, like the wind scatters chaff.
\q1

Yahweh continues to say, "You people of Israel are my servants;
\q2 you are descendants of Jacob, whom I chose;
\q2 you are descendants of Abraham, who I said was my friend.
\q1

Summon the people who have eyes but acts as though they were blind;
\q2 summon those who have ears but act as though they were deaf.
\q1

That is why I will cause your priests to be disgraced;
\q2 I will allow others to destroy you people of Israel
\q2 and caused you to be despised."

Yahweh is God;
\q1 he is the one who created the sky
\q2 and created and formed the earth.
\q1 He did not want it to remain with nothing living on it;
\q2 he wanted people to live on it.
\q1 He says, "I am Yahweh;
\q2 there is no other God.
\q1

Gods and animals are all bowed down;
\q2 the gods can save neither themselves nor the beasts of burden;
\q2 the gods themselves are going into exile!
\b
\q1

You people of Judah, do not forget this;
\q2 keep thinking about it, you sinful people!
\q1

But they cannot do that, because they are like straw that is burning in a fire;
\q2 they cannot save themselves from being burned up in the flames.
\q1 They are unable to help you;
\q2 they are as useless as stubble that burns, but that fire will burn them up rather than let them enjoy the heat.
\q1

I knew that you people were very stubborn;
\q2 I knew that your heads were as hard as iron or brass.
\q1

This is what Yahweh, the one who saves you, the Holy God of us Israelites, says:
\q2 "I am Yahweh, your God;
\q1 I teach you what is important for you to prosper;
\q2 I direct you and lead you to do the things that you should do.
\q1

I replied, "My work has been useless;
\q2 I have used my strength, but I have accomplished nothing worthwhile;
\q2 everything that I have done has been in vain.
\q1 However, Yahweh can honor me as he pleases;
\q2 my God is the one who will reward me as I deserve."
\q1

They will not be hungry or thirsty anymore;
\q2 the hot sun will not beat upon them again.
\q1 I, Yahweh, will act mercifully toward them and lead them;
\q2 I will lead them to where there are springs of cool water.
\q1

Note that I have written your names on the palms of my hands;
\q2 I am always looking at the walls of your city.
\q1

My people of Judah, listen carefully to me,
\q2 because I command you to proclaim my laws;
\q1 the right things that I will do will be like a light for the people of all the nations.

You have experienced several disasters:
\q2 Your country has become desolate;
\q1 your cities have been destroyed;
\q2 many people have died from hunger;
\q2 many people have been killed by your enemies' swords.
\q1 Now there is no one to weep with you and sympathize with you.
\q1

Your children have fainted and lie in the streets;
\q2 they are as helpless as an antelope that has been caught in a net.
\q1 What has happened to them is because Yahweh has been very angry with them;
\q2 he has rebuked them severely.
\b
\q1

Instead, I will cause those who have tormented you to suffer;
\q2 I will severely punish those who said to you,
\q2 'Lie down in order that we may walk on you;
\q1 lie down on your stomachs
\q2 in order that your backs will be like streets that we can walk on.'"

But people will pierce him through and kill him because of the evil things that we did;
\q1 they will wound him because of our sins.
\q2 They will beat him in order that things may go well with us;
\q1 because they will whip him, we will be healed.
\q1

Your government will be strong because it will act justly;
\q1 no one will oppress you;
\q2 you will not be afraid,
\q2 because nothing will come near you that will make you fear.
\q1

By what he did, I showed my power to many people groups;
\q2 I caused him to be a leader and commander over the people of many nations.
\q1

Seek to know Yahweh while it is still possible for you to do that;
\q2 call to Yahweh while he is near!
\q1

I will cause people to put inside the walls of my temple a monument to them;
\q2 because of that monument, they will be honored more than they would have if they had children;
\q1 they will be honored forever.
\q1

"You surrounding nations have armies that are like animals in the forest;
\q2 come and attack Israel!
\q1

I will not accuse people forever;
\q2 I will not always be angry with them,
\q1 because if I did that, people would become weak;
\q2 all the people whom I created and caused to live would die.
\q1

Wicked people do not have peace in their inner beings;
\q2 they are like a sea whose waves are always churning up mud,
\q1

In our courts, the judges do not decide cases fairly;
\q2 no one is acting righteously.
\q1 In plazas where people gather together, no one tells the truth;
\q2 it seems that people are not allowed to say what is true.
\q1

I did that because it was time for me to get revenge;
\q2 it was time to rescue my people from those who had oppressed them.
\q1

Yahweh said, "These are my people;
\q2 they will not deceive me";
\q2 so he rescued us.
\q1

"Yahweh, I wish that you had come down from the sky;
\q2 you would have caused the mountains to shake with fear.
\q1

You did awesome things that we were not expecting you to do;
\q2 the mountains shook when you came down onto Mount Sinai.
\q1

Since long ago no one has ever seen or heard about a God like you;
\q2 you help those who depend on you.
\q1

All of your towns in Judah have become like the wilderness;
\q2 even Jerusalem has been destroyed.
\q1

No child will die when it is still an infant;
\q2 all people will live until they are very old.
\q1 People will consider that anyone who is a hundred years old is still young;
\q2 they will consider that anyone who dies who is younger than that has been cursed.
\q1

Before they call to me to help them, I will answer;
\q2 I will answer their prayers while they are still praying for me to do something for them.
\q1
